 multiple values for a parameter.\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/amberframework/amber/blob/master/src/amber/router/params_parser.cr#L146-L147\r\n```crystal\r\n      HTTP::Params.parse(values) do |key, value|\r\n        params[key] = value\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis always overwrites previous values where `params` is a `Amber::Router::Params < Hash(String, String)` .\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n```crystal\r\nrequire \"amber\"\r\n\r\nrequest  = HTTP::Request.new(\"GET\", \"/?foo=bar&foo=baz\")\r\nresponse = HTTP::Server::Response.new(IO::Memory.new)\r\ncontext  = HTTP::Server::Context.new(request, response)\r\ncontext.params[\"foo\"] # => \"baz\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n\r\nWe should provide another method to **fetch all** values like `Rails`, `Crystal`, `Kemal` and any other libraries.\r\n\r\n**Crystal**\r\n```crystal\r\nrequire \"http/params\"\r\n\r\nparams = HTTP::Params.parse(\"foo=bar&foo=baz\")\r\nparams.fetch(\"foo\")     # => \"bar\"\r\nparams.fetch_all(\"foo\") # => [\"bar\", \"baz\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Kemal**\r\n```crystal\r\nrequire \"kemal\"\r\n\r\nrequest  = HTTP::Request.new(\"GET\", \"/?foo=bar&foo=baz\")\r\nparams = Kemal::ParamParser.new(request)\r\nparams.query[\"foo\"]           # => \"bar\"\r\nparams.query.fetch_all(\"foo\") # => [\"bar\", \"baz\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Versions\r\n\r\n- `Amber CLI (amberframework.org) - v0.6.4`\r\n- `Crystal 0.24.1 (2017-12-22)`\r\n\r\n**Amber** is a quite cool design, and I love it. 😄 \r\nI thinks it is time to polish it for production use! If no one has started this problem, I will try it.\r\n\r\nBest regards,","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/amberframework/amber/issues/591","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/amberframework/amber","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/amberframework/amber/issues/591/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/amberframework/amber/issues/591/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/amberframework/amber/issues/